---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Terms of Service" description="Terms governing use of the Podex service">
  <main class="py-12 md:py-16">
    <article class="container max-w-3xl">
      <header class="mb-10 border-b border-border-subtle pb-8">
        <p class="font-mono text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.24em] text-accent">Legal</p>
        <h1 class="mt-3 text-4xl text-text">Terms of Service</h1>
        <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-text-muted">Last updated: May 24, 2026</p>
      </header>
      <div class="space-y-9 text-text-secondary leading-relaxed">
        <section>
          <h2 class="mb-3 text-xl font-semibold text-text">Using Podex</h2>
          <p>
            Podex is a discovery service that indexes references discussed in podcasts and
            links them to their source context. By using Podex, you agree to these terms and
            the <a class="text-accent hover:underline" href="/legal/privacy">Privacy Policy</a>.
          </p>
        </section>
        <section>
          <h2 class="mb-3 text-xl font-semibold text-text">Accounts</h2>
          <p>
            An account is optional for public browsing and is required for saves, follows,
            alerts, and notification digests. You are responsible for access to your email
            account and for activity performed through your Podex session.
          </p>
        </section>
        <section>
          <h2 class="mb-3 text-xl font-semibold text-text">Acceptable Use</h2>
          <p>You may not misuse Podex, including by:</p>
          <ul class="mt-3 list-disc space-y-2 pl-5">
            <li>Attempting unauthorized access, disruption, or automated abuse of the service.</li>
            <li>Using the service to violate intellectual property, privacy, or other rights.</li>
            <li>Redistributing protected content obtained through unlawful means.</li>
          </ul>
        </section>
        <section>
          <h2 class="mb-3 text-xl font-semibold text-text">Content and Attribution</h2>
          <p>
            Podcast episodes and referenced works belong to their respective owners. Podex
            provides discovery metadata, source links, and limited context; it does not grant
            rights to underlying third-party content. Accuracy can vary and should be verified
            against the original source.
          </p>
        </section>
        <section>
          <h2 class="mb-3 text-xl font-semibold text-text">Rights Requests</h2>
          <p>
            Creators and rights holders can request corrections, suppression, or takedown of
            indexed material. We review requests and may restrict content while a request is
            assessed.
          </p>
        </section>
        <section>
          <h2 class="mb-3 text-xl font-semibold text-text">Availability and Liability</h2>
          <p>
            Podex is provided on an as-available basis. To the extent permitted by law, we
            disclaim implied warranties and are not liable for indirect, incidental, or
            consequential damages arising from use of the service.
          </p>
        </section>
        <section>
          <h2 class="mb-3 text-xl font-semibold text-text">Changes and Contact</h2>
          <p>
            We may update these terms by posting an updated version and effective date. Legal
            or rights-related questions can be sent to
            <a class="ml-1 text-accent hover:underline" href="mailto:legal@podex.app">legal@podex.app</a>.
          </p>
        </section>
      </div>
    </article>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>
